alerts.title: Beach Hazards Statement
regions: Coastal North Bay Including Point Reyes National Seashore
Southern Monterey Bay and Big Sur Coast
alerts.description:
...BEACH STATEMENT FOR SOUTHERLY FACING BEACHES...
A LONG-PERIOD SOUTHERLY SWELL GENERATED BY TROPICAL STORM
EUGENE COULD PRODUCE LARGE BREAKING WAVES ALONG SOUTH FACING
BEACHES SUCH AS SANTA CRUZ AND STINSON BEACH THROUGH THURSDAY.
ALTHOUGH SWELL HEIGHTS ARE EXPECTED TO DECREASE SLIGHTLY ON
THURSDAY THERE IS STILL A CONCERN FOR STRONG RIP CURRENTS AND
SNEAKER WAVES.
...BEACH HAZARDS STATEMENT NOW IN EFFECT THROUGH THURSDAY
EVENING...
* SEAS...SOUTH SWELL 3 TO 5 FEET WITH A PERIOD OF 13 TO 15
SECONDS.
* TIMING...THROUGH 9 PM THURSDAY EVENING.
* LOCATION...SOUTH FACING BEACHES SUCH AS SANTA CRUZ AND STINSON
BEACH.
* POTENTIAL IMPACTS...STRONG RIP CURRENTS AND POSSIBLE SNEAKER
WAVES. BREAKERS UP TO 6 TO 8 FEET.
